properties.name: Trailhead at Camp 4
properties.desc: The trailhead is located in the Camp 4 Campground. You can get off the shuttle at the #7 stop, cross the road, and walk a short 5-minute distance to the trailhead. This section of the trail begins with a lot of switchbacks. Though steep, it is actually well-shaded. On the way up, you will have great views of Half Dome and Awahnee Meadow. In about one hour (or one mile), you will arrive at Columbia Rock where you can take a short break and enjoy the surrounding sceneries.

properties.name: Columbia Rock
properties.desc: After departing from Columbia Rock, you immediately hike up into the landslide area above. Use cautions here as the sand on the trail is quiet slippery. After another 10 minutes of ascending, reaching the elevation of 5,200 feet, the trail begins to descend for about 200 feet in elevation before you meet the lower gate of Upper Yosemite Fall Trail.

properties.name: Lower Gate
properties.desc: After passing the lower gate, the trail becomes flat for about 500 feet before it ascends again. Here is also the best place to take shots of Upper Yosemite Fall and cool off in the mist coming off of it. After leaving the comfort of soothing moisture, you continue hiking up with more switchbacks, steeper and totally exposed at the mercy of direct sunlight. More attention is required for loose gravel on the trail. In about 2 hours, you will finally arrive at the upper gate and the ascent is finally over. There is a small stream near the upper gate for water provision.

properties.name: Upper Gate
properties.desc: After passing the upper gate, cross a small stream on the right and then follow signs for Yosemite Fall Overlook. In about 10 minutes, you can see the sign pole for the overlook near the edge of the rim.

properties.name: Upper Yosemite Fall Overlook
properties.desc: Make a left turn at the sign pole and you descend on the stairway to a small platform near the mouth of Yosemite Fall. It could be scary here as only the guardrail keeps you from falling all the way to the bottom of the valley. At the overlook, you can enjoy the view of the mouth of Yosemite Fall. Quite an impressive experience. When you decide to return, just take the same way back to the trailhead. If time is allowed, you can also visit the footbridge over Yosemite Creek near the mouth of the fall.
